{"title_page": "Gallician", "text_new": "{{For|the European language|Galician language}}\n[[Image:VanGoghMuralSchoolSelfPortrait.JPG|thumb|right|Murals from outside the school.]]\n\n'''Gallician''' is a village in the commune of [[Vauvert]] in the ''d\u00e9partement'' of [[Gard]], in the region of [[Languedoc-Roussillon]], southern [[France]]. It has a population of about 1,000 people. It is located 6&nbsp;km south of Vauvert, on the [[Canal du Rh\u00f4ne \u00e0 S\u00e8te]], which links the river [[Rh\u00f4ne]] with the [[Canal du Midi]] at [[S\u00e8te]].\n\n==Features==\nThe village contains a church, three large houses (Mas Beata, Mas du Notaire and Mas de Mourgues), a bakers, a small supermarket and two bar/restaurants, a bullfight arena, a camp site,<ref>[http://www.masdemourgues.com/photos.php?view=images/gallery/grins Mas de Mourgues camp site] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009002306/http://www.masdemourgues.com/photos.php?view=images%2Fgallery%2Fgrins |date=2007-10-09 }} accessed August 2007</ref> a cooperative winery<ref>[http://www.vins-rhone.com/pages/route-des-vins/deguster.asp?route=costieres&lng=en&rub=4A10&ville=GALLICIAN Cave pilote de Gallician at Vins-Rhone] accessed August 2007</ref> and the Van Gogh school for younger children.\n\nAt Gallician is the start of the Via Rh\u00f4na, a new long-distance cycle path which follows the Rh\u00f4ne, and links the village to Palavat-les-Flots in [[H\u00e9rault]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category-inline}}\n\n{{coord|43.644|4.296|display=title}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Occitanie]]\n\n\n{{Gard-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{For|the European language|Galician language}}\n[[Image:VanGoghMuralSchoolSelfPortrait.JPG|thumb|right|Murals from outside the school.]]\n\n'''Gallician''' is a village in the commune of [[Vauvert]] in the ''d\u00e9partement'' of [[Gard]], in the region of [[Languedoc-Roussillon]], southern [[France]]. It has a population of about 1,000 people. It is located 6&nbsp;km south of Vauvert, on the [[Canal du Rh\u00f4ne \u00e0 S\u00e8te]], which links the river [[Rh\u00f4ne]] with the [[Canal du Midi]] at [[S\u00e8te]].\n\n==Features==\nThe village contains a church, three large houses (Mas Beata, Mas du Notaire and Mas de Mourgues), a bakers, a small supermarket and two bar/restaurants, a bullfight arena, a camp site,<ref>[http://www.masdemourgues.com/photos.php?view=images/gallery/grins Mas de Mourgues camp site] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071009002306/http://www.masdemourgues.com/photos.php?view=images%2Fgallery%2Fgrins |date=2007-10-09 }} accessed August 2007</ref> a cooperative winery<ref>[http://www.vins-rhone.com/pages/route-des-vins/deguster.asp?route=costieres&lng=en&rub=4A10&ville=GALLICIAN Cave pilote de Gallician at Vins-Rhone] accessed August 2007</ref> and the Van Gogh school for younger children.\n\nAt Gallician is the start of the Via Rh\u00f4na, a new long-distance cycle path which follows the Rh\u00f4ne, and links the village to Palavat-les-Flots in [[H\u00e9rault]].\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat-inline}}\n\n{{coord|43.644|4.296|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Occitanie]]\n\n\n{{Gard-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eExternal links:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gallician"}
{"title_page": "Gagel", "text_new": "{{Infobox German location\n|type = Ortsteil\n|Municipality = [[Altm\u00e4rkische H\u00f6he]]\n|image_photo         = \n|image_coa              = kein\n|coordinates         = {{coord|52|51|N|11|34|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|state          = Sachsen-Anhalt\n|district           = Stendal\n|elevation                = 34\n|area              = 7.33\n|population           = 125\n|Stand               = 2006-12-31\n|postal_code                 = 39606\n|area_code             = 039391\n|licence                 = SDL\n|website             = [http://www.vgem-seehausen.de/verzeichnis/objekt.php?mandat=18788 www.vgem-seehausen.de]\n}}\n\n'''Gagel''' is a village and a former municipality in the [[Stendal (district)|district of Stendal]], in [[Saxony-Anhalt]], [[Germany]]. Since 1 January 2010, it is part of the municipality [[Altm\u00e4rkische H\u00f6he]].\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Villages in Saxony-Anhalt]]\n[[Category:Province of Saxony]]\n\n\n{{Stendal-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox German location\n|type = Ortsteil\n|Municipality = [[Altm\u00e4rkische H\u00f6he]]\n|image_photo         = \n|image_coa              = kein\n|coordinates         = {{coord|52|51|N|11|34|E|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n|state          = Sachsen-Anhalt\n|district           = Stendal\n|elevation                = 34\n|area              = 7.33\n|population           = 125\n|Stand               = 2006-12-31\n|postal_code                 = 39606\n|area_code             = 039391\n|licence                 = SDL\n|website             = [http://www.vgem-seehausen.de/verzeichnis/objekt.php?mandat=18788 www.vgem-seehausen.de]\n}}\n\n'''Gagel''' is a village and a former municipality in the [[Stendal (district)|district of Stendal]], in [[Saxony-Anhalt]], [[Germany]]. Since 1 January 2010, it is part of the municipality [[Altm\u00e4rkische H\u00f6he]].\n\n[[Category:Villages in Saxony-Anhalt]]\n[[Category:Province of Saxony]]\n\n{{Stendal-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gagel"}
{"title_page": "Alex Adomako-Mensah", "text_new": "\n\n{{Infobox MP\n| honorific-prefix    = Hon.\n| name                = Alex Adomako-Mensah\n| image               = File:Alex_Adomako_-_Mensah.jpg\n| alt                 = Alex Adomako-Mensah\n| constituency_MP     = Sekyere Afram Plains Constituency\n| parliament          = Ghana\n| president2          = [[Nana Akufo-Addo]]\n| president3          = [[John Atta Mills]]<br/>[[John Dramani Mahama|John Mahama]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1962|11|05|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Kumawu]], [[Ashanti Region]], [[Ghana]]\n| nationality         = [[Ghanaian nationality law|Ghanaian]]\n| party               = [[National Democratic Congress (Ghana)|National Democratic Congress]]\n| occupation          = Politician\n| profession          = [[Banker]]/ [[ Administrator]]\n| committees          = Finance Committee,Food and Cocoa Affairs Committee\n}}\n'''Alex Adomako-Mensah''' (born 5 November 1962) is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] male politician and [[Member of parliament|Member of Parliament]] for Sekyere Afram Plains Constituency in the [[Ashanti Region]], [[Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=220|title=Parliament of Ghana|last=Ghana|first=ICT Dept. Office of Parliament |website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nHe was born on 5 November 1962 and hails from [[Kumawu]] in the Ashanti Region.\n\n== Education ==\nAlex Adomako-Mensah earned his MBA in (UK) from the&nbsp;[[University of Leicester]], in 2001. He became an Associate Member (ACIM) of the  [[Chartered Institute of Marketing]], UK in 2003 and was honored a Member of the [[Chartered Management Institute]] (MCMI) by [[Chartered Institute of Marketing]], UK in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/republic/parliamentatian.php?ID=23|title=Ghana Parliament member Alex Adomako-Mensah|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Political life ==\nHe is a member of the [[National Democratic Congress (Ghana)|National Democratic Congress]] who was voted as part of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election in 2016]] to represent Sekyere Afram plains. He won the seat with 5,664 votes out of the 9,275 valid votes cast generating 60.85% of the total votes cast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.graphic.com.gh/elections/constituency-details/2016/sekyere-afram-plains|title=Ghana  Election sekyere-afram-plains Constituency Results|last=technologies|first=Esolz|work=Graphic Online|language=en|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanaelections.peacefmonline.com/pages/2016/ashanti/311/|title=Ghana Election 2016 Results - Sekyere Afram Plains Constituency|last=FM|first=Peace|website=Ghana Elections - Peace FM|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Robbery Attack ==\nOn August 14, 2017, the MP was attacked by an some unidentified arm robbers on his way from Kumasi heading towards Kumawu in the evening.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/politics/suspected-robbers-attack-mp-for-sekyere-afram-plains.html|title=Ghana news: Suspected robbers attack MP for Sekyere Afram Plains |last=Kyei-Boateng|first=Joseph|work=Graphic Online|access-date=2017-09-06|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dailyguideafrica.com/mp-robbed-gunpoint/|title=MP Robbed At Gunpoint |website=Daily Guide Africa |language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe is a [[Christians|Christian]] and married (with five children).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanamps.com/mps/details.php?id=2525|title=Ghana MPs - MP Details - Mensah, Adomako Alex|website=ghanamps.com|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Adomako-Mensah, Alex}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian bankers]]\n[[Category:People from Ashanti Region]]\n[[Category:National Democratic Congress (Ghana) politicians]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2009\u20132013]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2013\u20132017]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Leicester]]\n", "text_old": "\n\n{{Infobox MP\n| honorific-prefix    = Hon.\n| name                = Alex Adomako-Mensah\n| image               = File:Alex_Adomako_-_Mensah.jpg\n| alt                 = Alex Adomako-Mensah\n| constituency_MP     = Sekyere Afram Plains Constituency\n| parliament          = Ghana\n| president2          = [[Nana Akufo-Addo]]\n| president3          = [[John Atta Mills]]<br/>[[John Dramani Mahama|John Mahama]]\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1962|11|05|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Kumawu]], [[Ashanti Region]], [[Ghana]]\n| nationality         = [[Ghanaian nationality law|Ghanaian]]\n| party               = [[National Democratic Congress (Ghana)|National Democratic Congress]]\n| occupation          = Politician\n| profession          = [[Banker]]/ Administrator\n| committees          = Finance Committee,Food and Cocoa Affairs Committee\n}}\n'''Alex Adomako-Mensah''' (born 5 November 1962) is a [[Ghanaian people|Ghanaian]] male politician and [[Member of parliament|Member of Parliament]] for Sekyere Afram Plain Constituency in the [[Ashanti Region]], [[Ghana]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.parliament.gh/mps?mp=220|title=Parliament of Ghana|last=Ghana|first=ICT Dept. Office of Parliament |website=www.parliament.gh|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Early life ==\nHe was born on 5 November 1962 and hails from [[Kumawu]] in the Ashanti Region.\n\n== Education ==\nAlex Adomako-Mensah earned his MBA in (UK) from the&nbsp;[[University of Leicester]], in 2001. He became an Associate Member (ACIM) of the  [[Chartered Institute of Marketing]], UK in 2003 and was honored a Member of the [[Chartered Management Institute]] (MCMI) by [[Chartered Institute of Marketing]], UK in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/republic/parliamentatian.php?ID=23|title=Ghana Parliament member Alex Adomako-Mensah|website=www.ghanaweb.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Political life ==\nHe is a member of the [[National Democratic Congress (Ghana)|National Democratic Congress]] who was voted as part of the [[MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election, 2016|MPs elected in the Ghanaian parliamentary election in 2016]] to represent Sekyere Afram plains. He won the seat with 5,664 votes out of the 9,275 valid votes cast generating 60.85% of the total votes cast.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.graphic.com.gh/elections/constituency-details/2016/sekyere-afram-plains|title=Ghana  Election sekyere-afram-plains Constituency Results|last=technologies|first=Esolz|work=Graphic Online|language=en|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanaelections.peacefmonline.com/pages/2016/ashanti/311/|title=Ghana Election 2016 Results - Sekyere Afram Plains Constituency|last=FM|first=Peace|website=Ghana Elections - Peace FM|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Robbery Attack ==\nOn August 14, 2017, the MP was attacked by an some unidentified arm robbers on his way from Kumasi heading towards Kumawu in the evening.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.graphic.com.gh/news/politics/suspected-robbers-attack-mp-for-sekyere-afram-plains.html|title=Ghana news: Suspected robbers attack MP for Sekyere Afram Plains |last=Kyei-Boateng|first=Joseph|work=Graphic Online|access-date=2017-09-06|language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dailyguideafrica.com/mp-robbed-gunpoint/|title=MP Robbed At Gunpoint |website=Daily Guide Africa |language=en-US|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nHe is a [[Christians|Christian]] and married (with five children).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ghanamps.com/mps/details.php?id=2525|title=Ghana MPs - MP Details - Mensah, Adomako Alex|website=ghanamps.com|access-date=2017-09-06}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Adomako-Mensah, Alex}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1962 births]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian bankers]]\n[[Category:People from Ashanti Region]]\n[[Category:National Democratic Congress (Ghana) politicians]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2009\u20132013]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2013\u20132017]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian MPs 2017\u2013]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Leicester]]\n", "name_user": "Kobby Dankwah", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alex_Adomako-Mensah"}
